#: ../../../userspace-api/spec_ctrl.rst:3
msgid "Speculation Control"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/spec_ctrl.rst:5
msgid ""
"Quite some CPUs have speculation-related misfeatures which are in fact "
"vulnerabilities causing data leaks in various forms even across privilege "
"domains."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/spec_ctrl.rst:9
msgid ""
"The kernel provides mitigation for such vulnerabilities in various forms. "
"Some of these mitigations are compile-time configurable and some can be "
"supplied on the kernel command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/spec_ctrl.rst:13
msgid ""
"There is also a class of mitigations which are very expensive, but they can "
"be restricted to a certain set of processes or tasks in controlled "
"environments. The mechanism to control these mitigations is via :manpage:"
"`prctl(2)`."
msgstr ""

